OL,6,FPatrick's brother, Con, said: "It was
OL,7,Fnever about the money, you can't put a
OL,8,Fprice on life, but the police must be
OL,9,Fapologising for something."
OL,11,FEven though no police officers were
OL,12,Fever charged over the killing, Mr
OL,13,FRooney acknowledged the settlement
OL,14,Frepresented a vindication for his
OL,15,Fmother and late father.
OL,17,F"My daddy died in 2013, and on his
OL,18,Fdeath bed he asked us to keep going
OL,19,Fand don't let this go," he said.
